                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2915: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-01T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 1, 1930—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. President Machado will sign decree today restoring constitutional guarantees
                    which were suspended in Habana for twenty days on November 13 and also decree
                    reopening University of Habana. On Saturday troops were withdrawn from
                    University and yesterday Rodriguez Molina appointed new rector ad interim.
                    Legislation for University autonomy being studied.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
